{
  "stem": "4830.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I have taken all these opportunities.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I would say that I had a very thorough Jewish education, by Hungarian standards.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Bar mitzvah in Hungary was completely different from bar mitzvah here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Here, a bar mitzvah is an-- an opportunity for the parents to invite their friends and have a big evening out of that, usually with a large expense.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Hungary, the emphasis was to have the bar mitzvah in the synagogue, which was preceded by a six months very thorough preparation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had to learn far much more than my own share.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the rest of the celebration was simply that a number of friends of mine-- and nobody from the friends of my father and mother-- were invited for an afternoon coffee.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was a bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We did not--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At home, yeah.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, there was about 12 boys from the class who were invited, and that was it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Actually, I-- one of my best friends was not Jewish, who was sitting next to me in the Hungarian type of high school, which ran from grade 10 to-- from age 10 to age 18.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was sitting next to me, and we were very good friends.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was a strong believer of the final German victory, and-- but we were good friends, and we discussed it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I kept telling him that this is not going to happen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I tried to convince him that Germany's going to lose.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He tried to convince me that the new weapon that they will invent will give them world domination.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
